description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking Health Care Assistants to work in Harrogate Nightingale Hospital!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role offers Health Care Assistants the opportunity to support in the fight against Covid and work in the Harrogate Nightingale Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have worked as a Clinical Support Worker or Health Care Assistant for a minimum of 6 months and have an NVQ Level 2 in Health and Care, this role could be perfect for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Harrogate Nightingale Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift Pattern: &lt;/strong&gt;Long Day/Long Night Shifts (4 days on, 4 days off)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Bank work - flexible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay rates (tbc): &lt;/strong&gt;Day - £14.24&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Nights/Saturdays - £18.39&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Sundays/Bank Holidays – £22.55&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;Competitive Rates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Weekly Pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Accommodation, if needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Food paid for while on shift&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;                Potential for travel expenses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for compassionate, enthusiastic, and motivated Health Care Assistants to work within Harrogate Nightingale Hospital. A successful care assistant will be an effective team player and will be committed to equal opportunities and non-discriminatory practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, as a Health Care Assistant, you will be working closely with multi-disciplinary team members to provide a high standard of care for patients throughout their stay at Harrogate Nightingale Hospital. You will be responsible for implementing treatment and risk management plans and aiding patients through their recovery. Moreover, you will also be responsible for providing support and comfort to the patient during this difficult time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During your work as a care assistant, you will be expected to provide a high level of care to all patients in your ward or clinical area. This may include (and will not be limited to) moving and handling, personal care of patients, feeding patients and patient observations – this could be for a wide variety of patients. During your work at Harrogate Nightingale you will be working on acute medical units providing support and care to Covid positive patients. You must, therefore, have an excellent understanding of the correct use of PPE, and you must be willing and able to work in close proximity to Covid positive patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A successful candidate for this Health Care Assistant role will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 6 months experience as a Health Care Assistant or Clinical Support Worker in a UK care home, hospital or in the community (in the last 2 years).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 2 in Health and Care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability and willingness to work in close proximity to Covid positive patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full vaccination history (including two MMR vaccines, a full course of Hepatitis B, and a BCG vaccine).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pass pre-employment checks (including enhanced DBS, occupational health screening and entitlement to work checks).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
